FBIS3-10949 "drlat050_b_94002" FBIS-LAT-94-050 Document Type:Daily Report 14 Mar 1994 Haiti Brutus: Institutions Must Respect Electoral Legitimacy FL1403211194 Port-au-Prince Signal FM Radio in French 1130 GMT 14 Mar 94 FL1403211194 Port-au-Prince Signal FM Radio Language: French Article Type:BFN [Excerpt] The president of the Socialist Democratic Bloc in the chamber, Deputy Pierre Duly Brutus, told Signal FM that the country's institutions must agree to respect the principle of electoral legitimacy regardless of the personal motivations of President Aristide and General Raoul Cedras. Brutus also said that he applauds the fact that the National Front for Change and Democracy has understood the necessity of taking concrete action to get the country out of its rut. [passage omitted]
